snippet.title: Sling Media Slingbox Solo
snippet.description: An evolutionary upgrade of past Slingbox models, the Slingbox Solo remains an excellent way to stream your home TV programming to an increasingly wide variety of broadband-connected computers and smartphones.

snippet.title: 2014 Mercedes-Benz B-class Electric Drive
snippet.description: Taking advantage of its Tesla Motors partnership, Mercedes-Benz converts its B-class people mover to an electric drivetrain.

snippet.title: Bose Solo
snippet.description: Although its sonic talents are comparatively modest, the Bose Solo is an exceedingly handsome and easy-to-use sound bar.

snippet.title: Divoom Bluetune Solo wireless Bluetooth speaker
snippet.description: As far as tiny wireless speakers go, the Divoom Bluetune Solo stacks up well against the competition, with an attractive design, good features, and relatively decent sound.

snippet.title: Buy a full-size Han Solo in carbonite for $7,000
snippet.description: Clear some space in your living room, your "Star Wars" action figures will be dwarfed by this life-size Han Solo embalmed in carbonite.

snippet.title: 'Gear Solo' is Samsung's standalone smartwatch, report says
snippet.description: Samsung is tipped to be making a new smartwatch that doesn't need to be synced with a smartphone to make calls.

snippet.title: Get a Slingbox Solo for $39.99 shipped
snippet.description: That's just about the lowest price ever for this mega-popular TV-slinging box, which lets you watch live and recorded shows nearly anywhere.

snippet.title: Van Damme epic splits in space should be the final word
snippet.description: Good luck topping the latest parody of Jean-Claude Van Damme's epic splits Volvo truck ad. This time he's in space.

snippet.title: Sonar Solo visualizes trends in the Twitter fire hose
snippet.description: Bottlenose's free Web service dynamically exposes related concepts or trends for a query in real time, and allows users to continuously drill down via its visual interface.

snippet.title: Original Han Solo blaster from 'Empire,' 'Jedi' up for auction (pictures)
snippet.description: If you want to own a piece of "Star Wars" history -- and have $200,000 lying around -- you could buy this original Han Solo blaster. But, sorry, it wasn't used in the famous cantina scene.
